      },
      "layout_tag": "paragraph",
      "confidence": 0.9228969216346741,
      "reading_order": 11,
      "text": "The current system of managing records is too complex. The trend seems to be increasingly\nspecific, when we should be getting more general. Right now, people must work to understand\nthe system. We must spend too much time administering the system, labeling, and cleaning\nour files. Complying is a real burden, both for the individual and for the records\ncoordinators."
    },
